Dear Sir,&mdash;"ULO, Greatest seen," is certainly not
right (see page 144); neither is "AĴO, Work," entirely
correct. The one is a person, and the other a thing
denoted by the root, which is, in the one case, often adjectival, and
in the other verbal. The Text-Book&rsquo;s definition of ulo as
"one remarkable for" is somewhat exaggerated. One
possessing the quality of would be better (page 48).

The Text-Book does not give EL, out of, among the
